This scope has an actual low magnification of 1.30x and a high magnification of 4.00x. The field of view at 100 meters is 22.9 meters on low magnification and 8.8 meters on high magnification. The eye relief is 4.10 inches on low and 3.70 inches on high magnification. The scope weighs 11.50 ounces (325 grams).
The scope’s elevation and windage adjustment range are both 90 moa. The total length of the scope is 9.40 inches. The tube diameter is 30.00mm. The scope is mounted to the rifle in a Leupold Mark 2 Integral Mounting Systems (“IMS”) 30 mm mount. The mount is in matte black and is 1.40 inches high. I next fired three (3) rounds of Hornady Match .308 Winchester rounds firing a 155 grain A-Max full metal jacket bullet with a muzzle velocity of 2860 feet per second, to align the scope to the barrel.
I then adjusted the scope windage and elevation to zero at 250 meters and fired three (3) rounds of the same Hornady Match .308 ammunition. postcontent: Looking for a quick sale. CWP not mandatory. This FNS-9 from Fabrique Nationale is by far the best 9MM pistol on the market. I’ve owned it for 3 months and during that time have taken it to the range 3 times so total of 150 rounds have fired. It comes with everything.....original case, 3 magazines, all paper work, lock, etc. I’m asking $450. The FNS-9 4″ has a shape, length, width and unloaded weight that matches the Glock 19.  They’re both striker fired 9mm pistols.  There are some aesthetic differences, of course. Beyond that, the FNS-9 is almost exactly like a Glock 19…except slightly better in almost every way. On the FNS-9, all the controls are there and ready to go.  You can swap hands and continue to use the gun with no issues. There’s not much more you can ask of a pistol than to hold 17 + 1 rounds in a fairly compact, concealable package, that also boasts great accuracy and provides nearasdamnit flawless reliability. I don’t love the manual safety, but I understand why it’s there. The trigger has a secondary safety so you can choose to carry with the manual safety off if you’d like or buy the version without the safety altogether.
